				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">A "cel" is the term that I have used for the set of tiles that make up a particular frame of a critter's animation, derived from <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cel" class="postlink">the animation term</a>. For example, each cel of Mario's animation in Super Mario Bros. 3 is made up of eight tiles. The "sprites" are the hardware constructs used to display tile data. It takes four sprites to display the eight tiles of each cel of Mario's body.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

